
### to install github 
sudo apt-get install git-all

## to check version of git

git --version || git version


### to confiure github

git config --global user.name "your_username"

git config --global user.email "your_email_address@example.com"

git config --global --list


### Creating a local repository
Create a folder on your system. This will serve as a local repository which will later be pushed onto the GitHub website. Use the following command:

git init Mytest

### change the directory to newly created  local repository
 cd Mytest
 
 ####  create and then Add files and folders into newly created repository
 
git add README
git add sample.c


#### commit changes 

git commit -m "comment to changes made"


### get the remote acess of repository you already created on  your github account with the same name as local repository

git remote add origin https://github.com/yourUsername/yourRepository.git


### push the new files and folders created or chanes made in the exisitin one on to the github repository

git push origin master


Give usename and password for github account
